default.title: Benchmarking Heat across Campbelltown - aggregated measures
default.description: Contains location and aggregated heat measures captured via a network of more than 100 heat loggers installed in the council area.

default.title: Environmental sensors
default.description: Two environmental monitoring stations (EMS) were installed in December 2020. The EMS measures: particulate matter (PM 1.0, PM 2.5, PM 10), Nitrogen Dioxide, Carbon Monoxide, Ozone, temperature, relative humidity, and ambient noise.

default.title: Local Business Directory - Campbelltown
default.description:
Our local businesses are the heartbeat of our community. To support our local businesses, we encourage our community to use the local business directory to spend local, to keep jobs local.  

If you are a business in the Campbelltown City Council local government area add yourself to our business directory.

default.title: Services, Facilities & POI - Campbelltown
default.description: We provide a wide range of services and facilities including Libraries; Parks, Sport & Recreation; Child Care; Arts & Culture; Aquatics, Fitness & Indoor Sports; Facilities for Hire; Animal Care Facility; Sports Stadium & Athletics Centre.

default.title: Vulnerability
default.description: Vulnerability dataset provides statistics on the multiple stressors and shocks within the community including population, social, and economic factors. Data components include Population (Susceptible groups); Social (Language); Economic stress (Income, Household, Mortgage, Rental).

default.title: Waste Bin Collection Zones - Campbelltown
default.description:
Waste bin collection is just one of the key services Council do for our community.  Waste bin collection zones provide the collection day information.

Data Currency
Council will endeavour to refresh the dataset every six months until such time we can integrate our systems.  

This dataset is due to be refreshed in September 2021.

Data Accuracy 
The spatial accuracy of this information is reliant upon the NSW Spatial Services cadastre datasets. Dataset information is sourced from the Campbelltown City Council GIS dataset.  All information is provided and updated by the various stakeholders and custodians within the Council.
